#In this program, we are going to load an Image through Opencv by importing cv2. It is a basic approach to getting started with opencv extension. 

import cv2

### Reading An Image ###

img = cv2.imread('#File Location of the Image#')
cv2.imshow('frame', img)
cv2.waitKey(5000)

#If you are getting an assertion failed error (error 215) then please check your path of the image and extension of the Image.
#imread function will read the file through the given location.
#imshow function will make a new frame initially named as frame to display the image.  
#waitkey is waiting time/ display time for the Image.
